Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.28,0:00:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What's New in Cocoa Touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.94,0:00:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Eliza, and I'll be joined
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.48,0:00:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,shortly on stage by Josh
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.14,0:00:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Shaffer.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.81,0:00:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And today, we have a ton of
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.05,0:00:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,great new APIs to tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.45,0:00:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,about.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.05,0:00:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to start with some
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.35,0:00:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of the brand new productivity
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.46,0:00:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,APIs for iPad and iPhone.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.10,0:00:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, we'll show you some
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.73,0:00:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,of the refinements to the User
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.35,0:00:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Interfaces on these devices, and
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.65,0:00:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll talk about how you can get
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.07,0:00:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,these effects in your own
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.16,0:00:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,applications.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.78,0:00:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, we'll go through an
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.16,0:01:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,assortment of additions and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.99,0:01:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,improvements to existing APIs
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.31,0:01:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,across Cocoa Touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.33,0:01:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the most important
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.37,0:01:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,productivity API in iOS 11, as
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.98,0:01:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you heard in the keynote, is
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.47,0:01:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Drag and Drop.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.77,0:01:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This is an incredibly powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.51,0:01:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,API.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.74,0:01:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a video showing a couple
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.75,0:01:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of the things that it can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.84,0:01:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I can pick up an item, drag
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.76,0:01:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,it around.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.29,0:01:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I can tap to add additional
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.76,0:01:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,items to the drag.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.06,0:01:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The system remains fully
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.47,0:01:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,interactive while my drags are
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.99,0:01:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,in progress, and I can even drag
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.83,0:01:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,data between different
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.99,0:01:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,applications.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.22,0:01:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we're really excited for you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.08,0:01:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,guys to be adopting this API in
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.26,0:01:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,your apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.24,0:01:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And there are no fewer than four
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.66,0:01:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,sessions this week, telling you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.84,0:01:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,all about how to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.97,0:01:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, right now, I'm going to give
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.23,0:01:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you just a very brief overview
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.95,0:01:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,of some of the key components of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.14,0:01:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,this API, beginning with
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.20,0:01:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,enabling drags in your
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.68,0:01:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,application.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.73,0:02:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, suppose you have a custom
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.40,0:02:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,view with some sub-views, maybe
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.36,0:02:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,little icon like views, here,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.93,0:02:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that you want to make draggable.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.77,0:02:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What you'll do, is create a UI
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.98,0:02:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,drag interaction, which is a new
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.75,0:02:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,subclass of UI interaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.78,0:02:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And you'll attach it to the view
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.08,0:02:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that you want to allow the user
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.60,0:02:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to drag.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.61,0:02:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, a UI interaction is kind of
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.46,0:02:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,like a gesture recognizer.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.60,0:02:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You make one, you set a delegate
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.33,0:02:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,on it, you attach it to a view,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.16,0:02:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and then, the system takes care
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.74,0:02:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.73,0:02:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Your delegate will be called
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.16,0:02:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,back to provide information.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.62,0:02:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really quite easy to use.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.08,0:02:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So, here we would create a drag
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.60,0:02:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,interaction object, assign
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.06,0:02:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,ourself as a delegate, attach it
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.70,0:02:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to this view.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.20,0:02:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And we would also, do the same
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.89,0:02:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,for the other views that we want
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.11,0:02:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to make draggable.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.91,0:02:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.81,0:02:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,UIDragInteractionDelegate
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.06,0:02:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,protocol gives you a ton of
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.22,0:02:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,opportunity to customize what's
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.24,0:02:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,going on with this drag.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.72,0:03:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The one thing you absolutely
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.24,0:03:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,have to do, is provide the data
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.72,0:03:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,for the item that's being
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.78,0:03:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,dragged.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.54,0:03:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But apart from that, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.39,0:03:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,entirely up to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.32,0:03:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You can go with the system
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.02,0:03:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,defaults, or you can customize
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.97,0:03:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,all kinds of aspects of the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.30,0:03:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,drag.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.59,0:03:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, the lift animation, the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.07,0:03:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,previews, you can get callbacks
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.04,0:03:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,as the touch moves around on the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.81,0:03:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,screen and do things in
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.59,0:03:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,response.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.59,0:03:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's entirely open to your
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.10,0:03:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,application's needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.48,0:03:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the other major component of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.04,0:03:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Drag and Drop, obviously, is the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.59,0:03:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,drop component.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.78,0:03:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And to enable that, you also use
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.02,0:03:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,a new type of UI interaction
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.79,0:03:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,called the UIDropInteraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.21,0:03:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And you attach that not to the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.35,0:03:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,individual draggable views, but
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.72,0:03:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to the super view, the container
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.49,0:03:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,that's going to receive items
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.99,0:03:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,dropped.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.94,0:03:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Once again, you set a delegate.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.59,0:03:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And once again, this delegate
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.67,0:03:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,has the opportunity to do all
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.52,0:03:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,kinds of customization.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.98,0:03:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You can update your UI to make
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.60,0:03:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the other items get out of the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.89,0:04:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,way as the drag moves around,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.95,0:04:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,show a visual indication of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.23,0:04:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,where a drop would go, what
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.97,0:04:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,would happen if the user were to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.25,0:04:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,drop.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.51,0:04:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You receive the data when the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.06,0:04:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,drop is actually performed and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.01,0:04:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you can update your model in
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.44,0:04:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,response.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.75,0:04:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, you can also customize
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.96,0:04:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,all kinds of aspects of this
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.05,0:04:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,animation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.54,0:04:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You can customize the preview,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.83,0:04:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,during the drop, the drop
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.32,0:04:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,animation itself, it's really
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.69,0:04:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,very powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.79,0:04:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we're excited to see what
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.45,0:04:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,you will create with all of the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.41,0:04:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,power of this feature.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.66,0:04:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But to make it really easy to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.72,0:04:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,get started, the system has
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.38,0:04:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,built-in support in a number of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.42,0:04:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the existing classes that you're
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.77,0:04:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,probably already using.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.35,0:04:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to get this going with
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.59,0:04:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,TableView, CollectionView, and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.19,0:04:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the various Text and Web views,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.17,0:04:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,there's very little work for you
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.80,0:04:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to do, in addition.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.18,0:04:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,One other useful piece of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.49,0:04:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,integration on this system, is
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.74,0:04:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,with UIPasteConfiguration.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.74,0:04:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if your application already
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.27,0:04:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,knows how to handle the paste
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.95,0:04:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,part of a copy and paste
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.55,0:04:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,operation, there's very little
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.76,0:04:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,extra work that you need to do
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.51,0:05:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to make that same view a drop
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.53,0:05:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,target.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.71,0:05:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, here are the sessions on
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.46,0:05:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Drag and Drop.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.24,0:05:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And the first one is
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.28,0:05:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,introduction to Drag and Drop,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.48,0:05:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,right here, right after this
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.82,0:05:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,session.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.14,0:05:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, we really encourage you
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.26,0:05:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to stay for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.99,0:05:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow, we have Mastering Drag
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.49,0:05:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and Drop.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.21,0:05:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, there's an entire
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.31,0:05:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,session devoted to getting Drag
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.10,0:05:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and Drop working with your table
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.22,0:05:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and collection views.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.39,0:05:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And a really important session
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.15,0:05:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,on the various ways that you can
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.76,0:05:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,manipulate data with your drags
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.85,0:05:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and drops.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.58,0:05:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,There's actually a lot that you
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.81,0:05:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,can do there, that's very
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.71,0:05:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.20,0:05:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we encourage you to check
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.07,0:05:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that out, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.65,0:05:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.55,0:05:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the other piece of our
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.35,0:05:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,productivity enhancements on
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.99,0:05:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,iPad and iPhone is File
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.88,0:05:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Management.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.57,0:05:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We're introducing this wonderful
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.10,0:05:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,view controller that allows your
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.09,0:05:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,users to browse their documents,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.36,0:05:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,right in your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.73,0:05:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And this gives them access not
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.20,0:05:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,only to the local documents in
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.21,0:05:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,your app's documents folder, but
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.79,0:05:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,also, to documents stored on the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.35,0:05:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,cloud in iCloud Drive, and also
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.74,0:05:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in participating third party
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.26,0:05:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,cloud storage services.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.16,0:06:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,To make one of these.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.93,0:06:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the class is called
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.14,0:06:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,UIDocumentBrowserViewController.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.83,0:06:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And to make one, you pass it in
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.21,0:06:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,array of the file types that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.23,0:06:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,your app knows how to handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.92,0:06:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That way, the user can't open a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.25,0:06:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,file using this API that your
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.40,0:06:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,app doesn't know what to do
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.19,0:06:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,with.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.01,0:06:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And this class is actually quite
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.78,0:06:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,customizable.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.27,0:06:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The appearance can be changed in
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.70,0:06:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,a variety of ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.76,0:06:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can also set different
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.94,0:06:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,behaviors to occur as the user
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.08,0:06:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,navigates their files and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.28,0:06:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,selects one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.44,0:06:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,As I mentioned, this gives you
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.55,0:06:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,access both to local storage,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.43,0:06:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and documents stored on the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.78,0:06:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,cloud.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.99,0:06:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And that comes with one
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.81,0:06:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,important caveat that's really
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.53,0:06:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,important to keep in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.00,0:06:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is that you can no longer
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.84,0:06:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,depend on your application being
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.74,0:06:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the only one touching a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.17,0:06:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,particular file at a given time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.26,0:06:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's really crucial to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.77,0:06:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,coordinate file access with
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.69,0:06:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,documents that you're accessing
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.07,0:06:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,using this class.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.11,0:07:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can do that by using
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.15,0:07:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,NSFileCoordinator, directly, or
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.92,0:07:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,by sub-classing UIDocument,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.32,0:07:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,which builds in a lot of file
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.59,0:07:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,coordination behavior for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.25,0:07:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,To hear more about this class
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.41,0:07:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and other document based topics,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.48,0:07:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,please check out this session on
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.85,0:07:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Thursday.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.20,0:07:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, I'm going to invite
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.95,0:07:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Josh onstage, to talk us through
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.16,0:07:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,some of the UI refinements in
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.84,0:07:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.52,0:07:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.59,0:07:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,>> All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.94,0:07:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, Eliza.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.27,0:07:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there's a lot of really
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.02,0:07:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,great enhancements to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.02,0:07:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,productivity APIs in iOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.85,0:07:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But we've also got some really
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.38,0:07:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,great UI refinements, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.06,0:07:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And I want to talk through a
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.25,0:07:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,bunch of them, starting with one
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.81,0:07:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,of the most visible, which is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.08,0:07:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the new large title at the top
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.17,0:07:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,of the navigation bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.99,0:07:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the most visible
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.15,0:07:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,change that you'll probably
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.26,0:07:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,immediately notice, when you
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.45,0:07:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,start using iOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.82,0:07:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It includes this new large
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.89,0:07:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,prominent title displayed at the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.18,0:07:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,top.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.92,0:07:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Along, with a new unified search
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.70,0:07:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,field design that integrates it
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.36,0:08:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,right in the bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.94,0:08:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So, while your content is
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.06,0:08:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,scrolled to the top, you're
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.51,0:08:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,going to be able to have easy
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.58,0:08:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,visibility of the large title
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.95,0:08:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that tell exactly where you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.22,0:08:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and easier access to the search
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.93,0:08:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,field.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.21,0:08:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's now pulled down a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.38,0:08:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,little bit farther than where it
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.73,0:08:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,usually would have been, in the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.70,0:08:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,past.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.01,0:08:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,However, to maximize the area
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.74,0:08:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,available for displaying your
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.02,0:08:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,actual content, as you start
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.05,0:08:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,scrolling, both of these will
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.67,0:08:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,collapse in order to maximize
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.67,0:08:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the space below the bar, so you
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.28,0:08:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,can see as much content as
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.54,0:08:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.74,0:08:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,First, the search bar will
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.21,0:08:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,collapse itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.19,0:08:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, the large title will
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.87,0:08:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,scroll up under the bar, and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.33,0:08:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll end up with a view that
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.42,0:08:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,looks very much like what you
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.42,0:08:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,were used to, prior to iOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.38,0:08:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, UINavigationController will
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.29,0:08:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically find the main
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.18,0:08:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,primary content scroll view
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.01,0:08:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,inside of your currently visible
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.34,0:08:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,view controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.40,0:08:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And track its content offset to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.15,0:08:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,make sure that it can do this on
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.24,0:08:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,your behalf.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.32,0:08:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in most cases, there's
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.32,0:08:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,actually not a lot of work that
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.68,0:08:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you need to do, in order to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.98,0:08:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,adopt that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.00,0:08:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Enabling all this behavior is
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.37,0:08:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,actually really straightforward.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.13,0:09:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There's one new property on
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.40,0:09:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,UINavigationBar called
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.96,0:09:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,prefersLargeTitle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.03,0:09:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you just set that to yes,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.19,0:09:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to get the large
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.02,0:09:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,title appearance and
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.25,0:09:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,NavigationController will
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.47,0:09:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically do that tracking
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.79,0:09:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that we just talked about.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.67,0:09:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Finding your scroll view,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.33,0:09:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,tracking its offset, and
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.62,0:09:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,handling the shrinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.04,0:09:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the second thing is a new
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.61,0:09:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,property on UINavigationItem.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.78,0:09:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And this lets you control the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.02,0:09:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,appearance of the large title
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.26,0:09:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,for every level of your
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.52,0:09:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,navigation hierarchy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.22,0:09:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So, not every level, as you're
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.79,0:09:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,pushing view controllers onto
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.98,0:09:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the Navstack, needs to display
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.40,0:09:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the large title.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.54,0:09:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And in fact, many often do not.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.97,0:09:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can control at each
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.53,0:09:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,level using this navigation item
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.18,0:09:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,property, whether the large
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.78,0:09:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,title, or the older more small
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.99,0:09:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,traditional style is what you'll
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.31,0:09:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,see at any given point.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.72,0:09:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Adopting the searchController
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.96,0:09:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,appearance is also, really easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.65,0:09:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You can just use this new
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.56,0:09:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,searchController property, in
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.33,0:09:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,order to get that new appearance
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.17,0:09:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the new behaviors.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.74,0:09:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, traditionally in the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.98,0:09:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you would have taken your
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.79,0:09:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,navigation bar and probably
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.72,0:09:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,included it as part of your
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.80,0:09:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,content, maybe made it the table
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.50,0:10:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,header view for your
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.24,0:10:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,UITableView.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.58,0:10:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, instead of doing that,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.74,0:10:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,because the new appearance looks
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.79,0:10:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,more like it's part of the bar,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.48,0:10:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,you can just use this property
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.76,0:10:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and you'll get all those
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.43,0:10:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,behaviors.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.38,0:10:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Now generally, the first view on
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.36,0:10:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,your navigation stack is the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.86,0:10:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,only one that you would use the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.14,0:10:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,large title for.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.65,0:10:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a general bit of
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.16,0:10:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,guidance for designing your apps
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.43,0:10:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to use these large titles.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.20,0:10:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, as you push in to a second
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.87,0:10:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,level view and keep navigating
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.81,0:10:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,deeper, you'd usually use the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.55,0:10:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,more smaller traditional size.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.64,0:10:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a great starting point
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.74,0:10:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,for your designs, but as we just
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.22,0:10:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,mentioned, it is fully under
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.73,0:10:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,your control via the API, so you
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.63,0:10:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,can do the right thing for your
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.89,0:10:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,app.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.97,0:10:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And in fact, if you look through
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.40,0:10:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,some of ours, you'll find that
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.60,0:10:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Mail, for instance, uses the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.01,0:10:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,large title at the first two
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.37,0:10:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.31,0:10:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll also notice that the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.90,0:10:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,refresh control is now
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.12,0:10:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,integrated in this new, single,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.90,0:10:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,large title.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.17,0:10:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you use a UI refresh
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.55,0:10:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,control in your app to get your
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.00,0:10:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Pull to Refresh behavior, this
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.51,0:10:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,will actually happen
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.23,0:10:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.02,0:10:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there's no additional work
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.07,0:10:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to do to get that
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.29,0:11:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,visual integration with the bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.69,0:11:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,One important thing to note
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.82,0:11:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,about these large titles and the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.25,0:11:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,bar is that they're actually
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.85,0:11:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,part of the navigation bar, not
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.53,0:11:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,part of your content view.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.06,0:11:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result, the navigation bar
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.54,0:11:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,itself, is actually quite a bit
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.95,0:11:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,taller than you might normally
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.13,0:11:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,be used to from previous
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.59,0:11:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,releases of iOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.01,0:11:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And in fact, it can now change
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.36,0:11:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,height as the content scrolls.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.67,0:11:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, it's larger
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.91,0:11:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,while the large title is
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.65,0:11:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,visible.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.14,0:11:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, as the user scrolls
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.58,0:11:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and the large title disappears,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.79,0:11:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the navigation bar takes on a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.04,0:11:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,more traditional height as you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.13,0:11:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,would normally be used to.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.99,0:11:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you might initially be
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.87,0:11:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,concerned that this could be
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.92,0:11:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,complicated to deal with.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.43,0:11:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But the teams have been working
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.49,0:11:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,really hard to make sure that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.73,0:11:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,this is as easy as possible to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.36,0:11:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,deal with, in your apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.54,0:11:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And in most cases, it can
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.66,0:11:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,actually be handled
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.41,0:11:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically on your behalf,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.96,0:11:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,with no additional work.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.35,0:11:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,UINavigationController does a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.72,0:11:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,lot of this for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.50,0:11:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, to make it easier, though,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.90,0:11:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to find out as these bars change
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.90,0:11:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,height, there's a new property
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.60,0:11:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,on UIView, that's actually
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.17,0:11:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,really generally useful and can
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.74,0:12:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,apply across your entire
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.98,0:12:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,application.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.50,0:12:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the new safeAreaInset
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.61,0:12:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,property.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.26,0:12:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So, safeAreaInset lets you know
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.24,0:12:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the area of your content that is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.26,0:12:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,visible underneath anything that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.51,0:12:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,might be obscured by bars.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.87,0:12:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can reliably and easily
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.33,0:12:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,place your content in the area
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.77,0:12:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that will be visible and not
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.25,0:12:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,obstructed by any of these other
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.22,0:12:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,system UIs, like the bar at the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.15,0:12:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,top and bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.82,0:12:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, with this information, you
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.75,0:12:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,can easily do that layout.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.32,0:12:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And as the bar changes height
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.77,0:12:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,while the user scrolls, the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.24,0:12:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,safeAreaInset will grow so that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.14,0:12:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you can easily stay below the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.59,0:12:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.46,0:12:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if your view is overlapped
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.00,0:12:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,by a toolbar or a tab bar on the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.61,0:12:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,bottom, you're going to find
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.99,0:12:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that the safeAreaInset has a
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.21,0:12:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,value for its bottom, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.86,0:12:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So that you can be sure that you
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.95,0:12:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,know the exact area, top and
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.50,0:12:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,bottom, that you can safely
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.52,0:12:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,display content in.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.70,0:12:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The safeAreaInsets are really
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.21,0:12:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,easy to access, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.66,0:12:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there's three new properties
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.12,0:12:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,on UIView that make it easy to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.51,0:12:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,use this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.50,0:12:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The first is the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.03,0:12:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,safeAreaLayoutGuide.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.48,0:12:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, with safeAreaLayoutGuide,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.83,0:13:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you can easily integrate safe
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.14,0:13:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,areas with all of your auto
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.36,0:13:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,layout code.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.97,0:13:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can set up constraints
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.42,0:13:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,against this layout guide to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.87,0:13:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,position all of your content
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.22,0:13:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,within the safe area.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.65,0:13:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you're performing layout
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.65,0:13:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,manually, you may actually just
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.07,0:13:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,want to read the current safe
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.14,0:13:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,area values for a particular
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.39,0:13:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,point in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.55,0:13:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can do that with the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.39,0:13:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,safeAreaInsets property.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.27,0:13:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this is in the coordinate
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.16,0:13:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,space of your view, so it's
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.67,0:13:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,really easy to use to position
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.01,0:13:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,your content exactly where you
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.15,0:13:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,want.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.35,0:13:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, of course, if you're doing
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.80,0:13:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,manual layout, you'll also need
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.22,0:13:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to know when that changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.31,0:13:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, you can override the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.59,0:13:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,safeAreaInsetsDidChange property
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.88,0:13:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to find out when it changes and
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.27,0:13:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,adjust your layout.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.98,0:13:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, there's a lot of things,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.84,0:13:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because this is integrated
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.97,0:13:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout UIKit, that could be
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.27,0:13:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,handled automatically for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.50,0:13:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that previously would have been
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.40,0:13:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,more difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.62,0:13:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, UIScrollView can
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.21,0:13:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically include the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.39,0:13:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,safeAreaInsets as additional
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.20,0:13:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,scrollable padding at the top
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.92,0:13:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and bottom of your views.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.27,0:13:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that even if they're
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.24,0:13:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,underlapping the bars, you can
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.89,0:13:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,be sure that your content can
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.09,0:13:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,always be scrolled into view.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.10,0:13:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in previous releases,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.34,0:13:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,UINavigationController tried to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.86,0:13:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,handle some of this on your
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.72,0:14:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,behalf by calculating the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.13,0:14:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,overlap of the bars.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.11,0:14:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, setting a value on the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.79,0:14:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,contentInset property for your
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.27,0:14:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,UIScrollView.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.69,0:14:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you may have noticed that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.15,0:14:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,if you ever tried to set your
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.12,0:14:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,own contentInset for the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.34,0:14:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,UIScrollView, because you'd end
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.85,0:14:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,up fighting with
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.45,0:14:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,NavigationController over who
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.91,0:14:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,owned that current value at a
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.21,0:14:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,given time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.62,0:14:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,In iOS 11, that conflict is
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.24,0:14:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,gone, because
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.44,0:14:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,UINavigationController no longer
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.08,0:14:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,has to set the contentInset
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.29,0:14:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,property.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.31,0:14:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,ScrollView can set it on its own
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.72,0:14:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,behalf, by just looking at the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.71,0:14:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,safeAreaInsets, leaving the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.40,0:14:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,actual value of contentInset to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.23,0:14:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,be owned by you, for your
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.52,0:14:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,application needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.52,0:14:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.34,0:14:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So, UIScrollView tries to do the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.01,0:14:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,right thing, automatically, as
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.43,0:14:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,much as possible for this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.03,0:14:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's not always possible, of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.46,0:14:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,course, to get it right 100% of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.02,0:14:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.48,0:14:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And we know some of your apps
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.62,0:14:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,have different needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.10,0:14:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to help make sure that you
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.31,0:14:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,can always have the right
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.32,0:14:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,behavior, we have a new property
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.98,0:14:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,on UIScrollView that gives you
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.13,0:14:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,full control over how ScrollView
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.32,0:14:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,interprets these safeAreaInsets.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.43,0:15:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So, with this, you can tell it
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.45,0:15:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it should automatically
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.61,0:15:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,apply the insets, or just ignore
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.54,0:15:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,them, entirely.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.50,0:15:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that you can do the right
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.30,0:15:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,thing for your app, if it
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.33,0:15:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,happens to be the case that the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.43,0:15:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,automatic behavior isn't exactly
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.99,0:15:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,what you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.28,0:15:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you want to find out
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.30,0:15:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly what has happened, as
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.32,0:15:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,far as the ScrollView is
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.10,0:15:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,concerned, you can look at one
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.66,0:15:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,new property that can give you
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.16,0:15:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the current value of what it has
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.09,0:15:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,computed from safeAreaInsets,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.01,0:15:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,plus the sum of an contentInsets
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.73,0:15:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that you have set, yourself with
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.98,0:15:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the adjustedContentInset
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.05,0:15:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,property.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.48,0:15:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can find out exactly how
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.15,0:15:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,much space the ScrollView thinks
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.45,0:15:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,it needs to have for scrollable
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.68,0:15:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,padding.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.01,0:15:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So, so far, we've focused a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.14,0:15:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,on bars.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.67,0:15:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's also some other
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.89,0:15:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,refinements to other parts of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.04,0:15:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the UI, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.19,0:15:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll find that UITableViews
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.40,0:15:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,across the system, how have a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.98,0:15:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,new unified swipe delete
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.68,0:15:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,implementation that feels just
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.57,0:15:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,like what you're used to from
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.48,0:15:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the Mail app.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.67,0:15:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It includes support for multiple
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.17,0:15:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,actions on both the left and
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.24,0:15:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,right swipes, as well as single
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.37,0:15:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,gesture activation of the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.80,0:16:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,default one, with a full gesture
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.49,0:16:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,across the entire TableView.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.39,0:16:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's also really easy to use in
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.90,0:16:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,your apps, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.36,0:16:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So, with the new
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.41,0:16:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,UIContextualAction class, you
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.62,0:16:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,can specify the actions that you
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.86,0:16:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,want to be able to display in
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.83,0:16:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the TableView's rows.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.81,0:16:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Just providing the style that
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.95,0:16:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd like them to appear with,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.27,0:16:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and the title of the action, and
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.64,0:16:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,a block to invoke when they
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.18,0:16:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,should be run.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.69,0:16:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, with the new
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.44,0:16:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,UISwipeActionConfiguration
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.94,0:16:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,class, you can group together
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.70,0:16:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,multiple of these contextual
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.09,0:16:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,actions to display on the left
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.47,0:16:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and right side of individual
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.83,0:16:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,rows.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.52,0:16:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can also specify whether
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.77,0:16:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the first one should
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.65,0:16:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically be invoked when a
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.02,0:16:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,full gesture occurs across the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.73,0:16:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,entire row.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.88,0:16:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's very cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.12,0:16:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.22,0:16:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We do actually use this, now,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.50,0:16:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,across the system.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.15,0:16:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll find more actions in many
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.51,0:16:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,more places than before.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.87,0:16:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But do keep in mind, though,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.01,0:16:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,when you're using it, that any
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.39,0:16:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,actions that you put in the rows
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.93,0:16:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,behind the swipe actions will be
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.53,0:16:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,hard to discover than
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.91,0:16:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,something's that's visually
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.83,0:16:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,prominent in your application.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.80,0:16:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So, definitely use it as an
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.84,0:16:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,accelerator, but probably don't
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.51,0:17:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,make it the only way to perform
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.07,0:17:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,a particular action.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.16,0:17:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, outside of that, we've also
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.69,0:17:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,given you more control over the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.08,0:17:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,placement of separators in your
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.85,0:17:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,UITableView.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.00,0:17:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there's a new property on
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.67,0:17:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,UITableView that lets you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.61,0:17:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,control how separatorInsets that
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.32,0:17:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you set on the TableView are
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.60,0:17:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,interpreted.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.55,0:17:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You can indicate that they are
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.81,0:17:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,absolute values so they're
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.58,0:17:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,relative from the edge of the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.91,0:17:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,cell.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.71,0:17:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Or you can indicate that they're
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.02,0:17:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,meant to be deltas, offset from
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.97,0:17:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,where the TableView would have
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.05,0:17:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,otherwise placed the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.99,0:17:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,separatorInsets had you not
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.32,0:17:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,specified anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.73,0:17:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This makes it a lot easier to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.03,0:17:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,make sure that your separators
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.19,0:17:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,end at exactly where you want
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.49,0:17:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.75,0:17:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Regardless of the device that
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.95,0:17:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you're running on or the size
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.92,0:17:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,class that you're currently
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.69,0:17:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,running in.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.52,0:17:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.64,0:17:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there's a ton of new UI
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.28,0:17:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,refinements.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.42,0:17:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's a whole session that
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.76,0:17:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,can tell you about this and many
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.10,0:17:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,more.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.79,0:17:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the Updating Your App for
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.40,0:17:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS 11 session.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.61,0:17:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you should definitely check
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.39,0:17:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.73,0:17:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And to give you some ideas on
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.70,0:17:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the thinking behind the design
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.10,0:17:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of some of these new updates and
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.72,0:17:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,how you can best integrate them
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.91,0:18:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,into your apps, definitely also,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.81,0:18:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,check out the design session,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.41,0:18:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Design Studio Shorts 2, later
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.91,0:18:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,this week, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.78,0:18:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So, with that, I'll hand things
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.19,0:18:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,back to Eliza to tell you about
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.34,0:18:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,some more API enhancements
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.65,0:18:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,around Cocoa Touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.79,0:18:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.52,0:18:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.15,0:18:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.52,0:18:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to start with some of
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.86,0:18:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the new APIs in Swift 4 and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.22,0:18:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Foundation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.47,0:18:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there's actually a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.70,0:18:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,really exciting additions to
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.32,0:18:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Swift 4.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.15,0:18:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm only going to cover two
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.34,0:18:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,things, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.46,0:18:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The first is archiving Swift
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.42,0:18:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,native types.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.46,0:18:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you've attempted to use
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.77,0:18:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Swift 4 native types like
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.93,0:18:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,enumerations and structs with
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.89,0:18:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,code that needs to participate
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.74,0:18:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in, for example, NSCoding,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.66,0:18:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll have found that this has
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.51,0:18:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,been historically quite
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.56,0:18:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,difficult to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.53,0:18:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Swift 4 solves that problem with
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.40,0:18:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the introduction of a new
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.65,0:18:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Codable protocol.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.96,0:18:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And as long as the underlying
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.18,0:18:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,types in your enumerations and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.65,0:18:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,structs, are themselves codable,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.74,0:19:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,all you have to do to adopt this
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.29,0:19:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,is declare conformance to the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.90,0:19:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,protocol.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.69,0:19:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, Swift handles the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.07,0:19:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.48,0:19:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that allows these native
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.75,0:19:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,types to participate easily in
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.17,0:19:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,NSCoding.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.97,0:19:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And Foundation has also added
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.44,0:19:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,support for archiving to JSON
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.71,0:19:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and property lists.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.76,0:19:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Another really exciting edition
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.64,0:19:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to Swift 4 is the new KeyPath
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.83,0:19:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,type, and a literal syntax, and
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.43,0:19:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,getters and setters that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.54,0:19:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,correspond to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.94,0:19:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in the past, you specified
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.79,0:19:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,KeyPaths by hardcoding a String
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.04,0:19:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in your code, which as a result,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.88,0:19:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,couldn't be, if you had a typo
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.60,0:19:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,in it, it wouldn't be found at
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.65,0:19:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,compile time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.52,0:19:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, there's a new literal
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.78,0:19:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,syntax, this /, that allows you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.52,0:19:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to construct a KeyPath, and this
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.15,0:19:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,is a strongly typed object.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.72,0:19:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if I have a presenter
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.44,0:19:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,object, for example, that has a
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.64,0:19:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,couple properties, a
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.75,0:19:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,copresenter, which is another
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.97,0:19:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,presenter, and a name.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.59,0:19:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I can construct a KeyPath object
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.59,0:19:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,representing my copresenter's
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.19,0:19:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,name.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.25,0:20:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, I can use this new
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.81,0:20:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,square bracket getter notation
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.79,0:20:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to access that property on one
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.36,0:20:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,of my presenter objects.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.05,0:20:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in this case, accessing it
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.31,0:20:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,on an object representing me
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.24,0:20:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,would return the String Josh.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.16,0:20:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You can also forego making the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.33,0:20:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,KeyPath object as a separate
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.67,0:20:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,step and just use the literal
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.21,0:20:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,syntax in the getter.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.27,0:20:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And take advantage of Swift's
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.46,0:20:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,type inference, to leave off the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.35,0:20:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,type, if you do it that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.20,0:20:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this is very cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.57,0:20:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And Foundation has taken it one
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.80,0:20:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,step further by introducing an
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.16,0:20:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,updated way of using KVO with
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.22,0:20:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,these KeyPaths.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.11,0:20:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this is a picture of what
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.23,0:20:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you used to have to do to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.74,0:20:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,observe changes to a property on
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.61,0:20:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,one of your objects.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.68,0:20:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a little bit involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.16,0:20:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You had to override a method.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.76,0:20:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And because your Superclass
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.48,0:20:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,might also override that method,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.87,0:20:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you had to use a context pointer
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.71,0:20:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to disambiguate which one of you
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.41,0:20:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is getting it at any given time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.75,0:20:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was quite difficult to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.84,0:20:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,get right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.99,0:20:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, new in iOS 11, we have
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.90,0:21:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,block-based KVO.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.23,0:21:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We're really excited about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.52,0:21:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.72,0:21:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,If I want to observe the changes
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.58,0:21:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to my copresenter, I'm not sure
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.29,0:21:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,why I would, since it never
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.23,0:21:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,seems to change, I can do so by
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.44,0:21:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,simply setting a block and
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.76,0:21:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,observing one of these KeyPaths
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.40,0:21:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,using a literal syntax.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.71,0:21:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's very cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.24,0:21:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a lot of new topics in
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.75,0:21:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Foundation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.29,0:21:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And please check out their
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.65,0:21:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,related session, on Wednesday.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.13,0:21:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, deferring system gestures.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.95,0:21:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is a funny case.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.54,0:21:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you have an app that
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.70,0:21:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe, shows some content, and
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.88,0:21:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,shows its status bar, the user
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.78,0:21:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,can swipe down from the top to
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.25,0:21:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,bring in the notification
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.46,0:21:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,center.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.07,0:21:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if you hid your status
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.76,0:21:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,bar and the user swipes down
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.15,0:21:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,from the top, they'll instead
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.60,0:21:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,see this tab UI.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.42,0:21:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that case, your app will
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.54,0:21:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,actually receive the touches
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.88,0:21:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that are originating near the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.98,0:21:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,top of the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.12,0:21:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we did this in iOS 5, when
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.62,0:22:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,we introduced the Notification
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.85,0:22:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Center.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.06,0:22:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we wanted to make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.63,0:22:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that apps that might need to see
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.85,0:22:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,touches near the edges of the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.35,0:22:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,screen, could do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.07,0:22:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And we took the presence or
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.41,0:22:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,absence of the status bar as an
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.91,0:22:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,indication of whether your app
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.18,0:22:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,fell in that category.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.00,0:22:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So, then in iOS 7, we introduced
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.04,0:22:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the Control Center with a swipe
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.29,0:22:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,up from the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.93,0:22:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,If your app hid its status bar,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.10,0:22:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,we used the same rule and we
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.85,0:22:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,would show the tab instead of
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.27,0:22:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the control center.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.89,0:22:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that made a little bit less
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.34,0:22:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,sense, because the status bar is
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.58,0:22:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,at the top of the screen, not
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.69,0:22:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.22,0:22:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, the presence or absence
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.68,0:22:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,of the status bar shouldn't
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.55,0:22:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,really tell us very much about
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.96,0:22:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,what your app needs to see, in
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.23,0:22:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,terms of touches near the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.07,0:22:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.21,0:22:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the other problem with the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.29,0:22:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,status quo, here, is that your
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.04,0:22:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,users really want, when they
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.98,0:22:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,swipe near the edge of the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.06,0:22:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,screen, to see the system UIs
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.00,0:22:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,components appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.42,0:22:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what they expect to have
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.63,0:22:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.06,0:22:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So, unless your app actually
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.24,0:23:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,needs to get access to the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.40,0:23:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,touches near the edge, it's a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.71,0:23:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,better user experience to allow
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.03,0:23:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,those notifications that are in
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.90,0:23:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Control Center to simply appear
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.16,0:23:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.38,0:23:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in iOS 11, we're allowing
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.19,0:23:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you to make this explicit by
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.14,0:23:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,adding this new
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.82,0:23:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,preferredScreenEdgesForDeferring
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.40,0:23:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,System Gestures method.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.78,0:23:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If you override it in your
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.09,0:23:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,viewControllers, you can return
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.94,0:23:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,a UIRectEdge, which is a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.40,0:23:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,collection of different edges.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.89,0:23:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And we strongly encourage you to
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.48,0:23:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,only return edges that you want
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.34,0:23:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to protect from system gestures.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.57,0:23:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If you really need to see
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.90,0:23:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,touches that are right on that
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.79,0:23:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,edge of the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.26,0:23:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it will be a better
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.13,0:23:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,experience for you users to just
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.57,0:23:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,allow the system gestures to
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.63,0:23:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,happen as they normally would.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.06,0:23:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.11,0:23:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So, another topic where we've
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.82,0:23:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,made some improvements, is Auto
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.12,0:23:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Layout.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.42,0:23:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And in particular, the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.88,0:23:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,interaction of Auto Layout and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.40,0:23:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Scroll Views.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.07,0:23:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Scroll Views pose kind of a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.02,0:23:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,challenge for Auto Layout,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.18,0:24:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,because they represent two
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.68,0:24:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,different coordinate systems
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.09,0:24:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,mushed into one.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.31,0:24:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You have the frame of the Scroll
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.55,0:24:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,View, and then, you have the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.95,0:24:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,coordinate system of its
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.86,0:24:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,content.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.67,0:24:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is often larger than the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.08,0:24:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Scroll View, and is almost
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.51,0:24:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,always offset relative to the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.96,0:24:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Scroll View's origin.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.34,0:24:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when you're composing your
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.57,0:24:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,constraints for Scroll Views,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.82,0:24:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Scroll View has a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.12,0:24:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,know-how kind of built in, where
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.46,0:24:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,it guesses what you probably
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.63,0:24:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,meant.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.99,0:24:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And it tries to do the right
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.15,0:24:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,thing based on the constraints
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.71,0:24:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're composing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.94,0:24:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But in iOS 11, we're allowing
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.08,0:24:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you to make it really clear what
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.58,0:24:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,you mean and be completely
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.29,0:24:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,explicit about it, by
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.65,0:24:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,introducing two new Layout
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.05,0:24:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,guides on Scroll View.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.42,0:24:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,A contentLayoutGuide and a
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.92,0:24:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,frameLayoutGuide.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.64,0:24:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So, now you can construct
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.62,0:24:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,constraints that specifically
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.55,0:24:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,represent one of these
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.62,0:24:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,coordinate systems or the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.52,0:24:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.04,0:24:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this allows you to do
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.96,0:24:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,something really easily, that
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.18,0:24:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,used to be hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.37,0:24:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So, sometimes when you have a
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.36,0:24:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Scroll View and you have content
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.61,0:24:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that can zoom in and out.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.91,0:24:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You want the content to come to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.43,0:25:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,rest in the center of the Scroll
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.48,0:25:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,View as you're zooming out on
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.54,0:25:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.74,0:25:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Josh and I, a couple of
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.69,0:25:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,years ago, spent one-third of
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.52,0:25:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the WWDC presentation explaining
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.56,0:25:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,how you could get this effect in
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.78,0:25:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,your Scroll Views.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.86,0:25:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And up until recently, it was
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.65,0:25:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,actually really hard to do it
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.06,0:25:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,with Auto Layout.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.42,0:25:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, you can do it in two
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.14,0:25:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,lines of code.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.25,0:25:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,All you need to do is set the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.70,0:25:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,centerXAnchor of the imageView,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.05,0:25:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,or whatever the content of your
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.50,0:25:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Scroll View is, equal to the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.59,0:25:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,contentLayoutGuide's
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.47,0:25:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,centerXAnchor.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.28,0:25:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, you would do the same
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.40,0:25:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,thing in the Y coordinate.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.57,0:25:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, this will just happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.51,0:25:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.32,0:25:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.18,0:25:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Dynamic Type.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.80,0:25:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, dynamic type is a really
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.25,0:25:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,important feature on iOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.87,0:25:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's a picture of a whole
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.06,0:25:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,bunch of different dynamic type
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.28,0:25:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,sizes that the user may
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.92,0:25:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,configure, and how we're
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.23,0:25:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,handling it in our own Calendar
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.84,0:25:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,app.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.17,0:25:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So, here's a small setting for
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.58,0:25:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,dynamic type.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.94,0:25:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Larger. Larger.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.79,0:25:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Very large.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.42,0:26:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And there even are larger
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.06,0:26:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibility dynamic type sizes
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.71,0:26:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that can be selected.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.89,0:26:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this can pose a challenge in
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.21,0:26:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a number of ways to support in
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.92,0:26:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,your applications.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.87,0:26:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But for users who have chosen a
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.49,0:26:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,nonstandard dynamic type size,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.29,0:26:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a really bad user
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.60,0:26:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,experience if your app doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.06,0:26:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,participate or honor their
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.54,0:26:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,selection.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.48,0:26:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we've made a few
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.76,0:26:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,improvements to make it easier
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.92,0:26:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to do this correctly in your
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.11,0:26:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,applications.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.02,0:26:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And the first one has to do with
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.82,0:26:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,sizing your text.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.40,0:26:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So, suppose you have a 16-point
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.15,0:26:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,font that you're using for the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.57,0:26:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,standard type size.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.69,0:26:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you decide what font to
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.99,0:26:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,use if the user has a
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.02,0:26:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,nonstandard dynamic type
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.59,0:26:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,selection?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.09,0:26:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The old way of doing this was
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.88,0:26:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,you could ask UIFont for the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.34,0:26:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,preferred font for a given text
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.45,0:26:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,style, which.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.04,0:26:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's a number of text
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.05,0:26:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,styles, Body, Title, a variety
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.23,0:26:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,of them you can look up.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.06,0:26:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And this was pretty good,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.75,0:26:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,because it would get you a good
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.75,0:26:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,font for the appropriate place
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.19,0:26:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,in your application.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.19,0:26:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was a little inflexible,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.75,0:26:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,because what if you needed a
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.81,0:27:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,custom font?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.65,0:27:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just going to give you
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.43,0:27:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the system font, every time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.29,0:27:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What if you wanted to use a
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.09,0:27:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Monospace Number font in some
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.01,0:27:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,particular case?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.99,0:27:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Or just some font that, you
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.03,0:27:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,know, matched your branding a
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.62,0:27:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,little bit better.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.71,0:27:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,In iOS 11, we're introducing a
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.95,0:27:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,new class that solves this
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.13,0:27:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,problem, called UIFontMetrics.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.22,0:27:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And the way you use it, is you
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.80,0:27:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,create a FontMetrics object for
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.10,0:27:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the text style that you're
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.07,0:27:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,interested in.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.94,0:27:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You then, choose any font you
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.48,0:27:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,want, sized for the standard
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.51,0:27:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,dynamic type size.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.52,0:27:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, you can ask the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.89,0:27:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,FontMetrics object to scale that
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.78,0:27:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,font given the user's current
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.43,0:27:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,settings.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.69,0:27:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And that gets you back a font,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.69,0:27:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,any font you want, at the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.05,0:27:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,appropriate size to display.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.37,0:27:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, this is really cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.17,0:27:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So, just that, alone, doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.24,0:27:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,completely solve the problem,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.61,0:27:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,because imagine you have like a
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.55,0:27:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,custom button, or maybe a custom
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.18,0:27:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.76,0:27:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're putting some text
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.96,0:27:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,inside it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.81,0:27:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,How tall do you want to make
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.11,0:27:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that button?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.45,0:27:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,If the user has a nonstandard
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.75,0:28:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,dynamic type setting, it might
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.66,0:28:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,overrun the height that you've
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.11,0:28:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,made available.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.03,0:28:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So, UIFontMetrics has solved
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.02,0:28:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,this problem, as well, by
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.01,0:28:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,allowing you to scale arbitrary
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.41,0:28:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,layout values.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.10,0:28:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you create, once again, a
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.94,0:28:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,FontMetrics object.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.31,0:28:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You choose a height that would
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.36,0:28:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,look good at the standard
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.36,0:28:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,dynamic type size, and then you
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.84,0:28:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,can scale it based on the user's
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.35,0:28:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,current settings.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.94,0:28:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this is super useful for
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.14,0:28:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,your font sizing and layout.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.56,0:28:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we also have an addition to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.89,0:28:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Auto Layout to support dynamic
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.49,0:28:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,type, which we're pretty excited
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.67,0:28:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,about.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.50,0:28:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Suppose that I have two labels
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.44,0:28:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,with different fonts, maybe,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.28,0:28:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,laid out vertically.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.50,0:28:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've chosen a baseline to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.76,0:28:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,baseline spacing that looks good
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.22,0:28:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,at this font size.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.32,0:28:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, my user might have chosen a
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.15,0:28:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,larger or a smaller dynamic type
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.61,0:28:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,size.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.27,0:28:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And as a result, the spacing
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.59,0:28:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,might actually look quite a bit
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.15,0:28:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,too tight or too loose.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.52,0:29:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, with Auto Layout, there's
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.23,0:29:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,now a solution for this problem,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.11,0:29:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,which is that we're exposing a
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.36,0:29:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,way to access the system
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.96,0:29:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,recommended spacing.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.81,0:29:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And you do this by, first of
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.74,0:29:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,all, there's two ingredients.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.81,0:29:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to be doing baseline to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.04,0:29:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,baseline spacing, in order to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.30,0:29:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,inform Auto Layout that it
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.48,0:29:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,should take font sizes into
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.75,0:29:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,consideration.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.57,0:29:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I would make a topAnchor
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.29,0:29:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,using the lastBaselineAnchor of
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.73,0:29:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,my topLabel, and a bottomAnchor
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.45,0:29:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,using the firstBaselineAnchor of
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.80,0:29:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,my bottomLabel.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.23,0:29:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, I would use the new
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.72,0:29:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,constraintEqualToSystemSpacing
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.56,0:29:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,below method to ask Auto Layout
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.39,0:29:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to choose a value that will look
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.16,0:29:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,good, given the font sizes that
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.46,0:29:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,are being displayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.12,0:29:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And that will cause the text to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.60,0:29:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,adjust, so that's it's visually
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.26,0:29:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,pleasing at all of the different
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.48,0:29:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,dynamic type sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.54,0:29:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And this works with the Visual
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.94,0:29:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Format Language, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.14,0:29:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, we have the same two
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.08,0:29:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,ingredients.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.68,0:29:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We have the system spacing,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.28,0:29:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,which is provided by the dashes
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.51,0:29:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in my Visual Format String, and
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.71,0:29:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,then, a new baseline to baseline
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.22,0:29:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,option to pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.53,0:29:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that the Auto Layout system
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.82,0:29:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,will know to do this work for
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.41,0:29:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.84,0:29:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And it also works with
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.94,0:29:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,UIStackView, again, passing
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.34,0:29:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,those same two options.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.07,0:30:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to find out more about
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.32,0:30:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,building your apps with dynamic
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.76,0:30:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,type, please check out this
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.37,0:30:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,associated session, on Friday.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.21,0:30:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of good content, here.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.90,0:30:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.01,0:30:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Password Autofill.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.92,0:30:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my very favorite new
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.70,0:30:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,API, that we're introducing,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.97,0:30:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.35,0:30:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm really excited about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.45,0:30:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of you may have experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.71,0:30:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,a workflow similar to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.16,0:30:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my standard workflow
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.47,0:30:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,when I sign up for a web
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.45,0:30:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,service.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.72,0:30:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I sign up for the web service of
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.88,0:30:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,some kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.97,0:30:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I allow Safari to suggest a
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.71,0:30:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,password, which I dutifully
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.01,0:30:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,accept.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.38,0:30:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a nice strong password that
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.65,0:30:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I would never want type in a
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.73,0:30:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.15,0:30:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, the service says, ''Hey,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.71,0:30:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,download our app.'' And so, I
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.15,0:30:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,do.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.03,0:30:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I launch the app, and I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.72,0:30:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,immediately presented with this
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.05,0:30:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,password entry field.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.25,0:30:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, I've saved this
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.56,0:30:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,strong password in my iCloud
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.36,0:30:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Keychain.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.26,0:30:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I don't know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.66,0:30:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'm completely stuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.97,0:30:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I go back to the web
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.67,0:30:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,interface, and I say I forgot my
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.04,0:30:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,password.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.54,0:31:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And I reset the password to
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.56,0:31:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,something really easy like
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.70,0:31:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Password.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.56,0:31:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, I go in and I log in
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.76,0:31:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and I've got no security.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.23,0:31:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And I probably get hacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.30,0:31:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.83,0:31:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, starting with iOS 11, this
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.32,0:31:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,nightmare is going to end.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.51,0:31:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We are introducing a really
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.18,0:31:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,great new feature, where when we
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.53,0:31:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,detect that you're showing a
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.70,0:31:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,username and password field,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.76,0:31:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,this key UI will appear in the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.96,0:31:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,candidate bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.53,0:31:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you click on it you get a
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.31,0:31:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,list of all of your saved
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.09,0:31:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,passwords in the iCloud
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.81,0:31:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Keychain.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.85,0:31:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can go through and
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.95,0:31:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,select the right one.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.01,0:31:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that already is a better
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.65,0:31:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,experience than the one where
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.98,0:31:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you're completely stuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.18,0:31:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's not ideal.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.38,0:31:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,For a lot of users, they're not
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.46,0:31:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,really going to know what to do
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.51,0:31:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,with this list.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.93,0:31:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're like me, you have a
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.81,0:31:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,lot of passwords on this list.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.25,0:31:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And scrolling through it to find
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.39,0:31:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the right one might be a little
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.31,0:31:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,bit challenging.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.22,0:31:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there's a way that you can
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.18,0:31:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,make an even better experience
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.60,0:31:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,for your users, here.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.81,0:31:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is just a couple steps.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.94,0:31:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we what we want is for the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.60,0:32:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,correct suggestion to appear in
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.08,0:32:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the candidate bar, by default.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.39,0:32:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, you don't even need to
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.46,0:32:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,mess around with finding the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.89,0:32:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,right value in that list.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.54,0:32:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And to do that, it's just two
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.18,0:32:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,things.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.12,0:32:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to add one entitlement
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.99,0:32:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to your application, and a
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.00,0:32:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,couple of lines of JSON to your
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.08,0:32:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,web service.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.55,0:32:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And you might have already done
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.90,0:32:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,these steps to support universal
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.38,0:32:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,links.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.32,0:32:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you have done that, then
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.92,0:32:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,this really good UI will appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.46,0:32:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I tap on it, I simply
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.81,0:32:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,get my password filled in.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.93,0:32:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So, please for my sake, adopt
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.86,0:32:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,this in your apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.59,0:32:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We're really excited about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.87,0:32:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And go to the associated
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.36,0:32:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,session, tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.52,0:32:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.05,0:32:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.35,0:32:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a couple of improvements
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.68,0:32:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,to Asset Catalogs that we're
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.45,0:32:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,excited to tell you about.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.73,0:32:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Colors can now be added to Asset
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.45,0:32:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Catalogs, as well as icons.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.87,0:32:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can now make named
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.31,0:32:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.52,0:32:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.47,0:32:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And this allows you to easily
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.78,0:33:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,support wide gamut colors on the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.06,0:33:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,appropriate devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.72,0:33:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can create a wide gamut
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.09,0:33:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,color and add it to your Asset
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.34,0:33:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Catalog.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.73,0:33:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You can access it by name.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.81,0:33:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can also, make a
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.65,0:33:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,fallback color to be used in the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.09,0:33:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,sRGB Color Space for devices
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.55,0:33:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that don't support wide gamut.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.70,0:33:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can now, do the same
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.93,0:33:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,thing with your app icons.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.33,0:33:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So, app icons can now include
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.94,0:33:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,wide gamut colors, which will be
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.40,0:33:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,displayed on devices that
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.81,0:33:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,support the P3 Color Space.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.82,0:33:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition, you may find that,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.60,0:33:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,well, at least it's true for
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.52,0:33:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,certain apps, that the icons are
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.59,0:33:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,actually the largest aspect of
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.40,0:33:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,your app's footprint.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.73,0:33:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, by incorporating them in
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.88,0:33:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Asset Catalogs, we're now able
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.41,0:33:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to have them participate in the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.33,0:33:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,app thinning, which will
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.10,0:33:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,significantly lower your app's
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.85,0:33:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,footprint.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.35,0:33:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this is a really exciting
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.69,0:33:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,thing to adopt, and it will be
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.51,0:33:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,adopted by default in new
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.75,0:33:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,projects in iOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.07,0:33:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You can opt into it in existing
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.01,0:33:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,projects by adding a key to your
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.49,0:33:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Info.plist.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.69,0:33:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So, PDF-backed images.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.49,0:33:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,These are something that have
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.36,0:34:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,been possible for a little
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.85,0:34:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,while, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.47,0:34:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's a new option when
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.75,0:34:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you add an image to your Asset
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.24,0:34:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Catalog, that's PDF-backed.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.31,0:34:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You're given the option to
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.91,0:34:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,preserve the vector data.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.20,0:34:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this is new in iOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.99,0:34:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's a really powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.02,0:34:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,feature.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.87,0:34:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,If you click that box, the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.69,0:34:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,vector data will be shipped with
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.83,0:34:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,your application.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.95,0:34:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Which, on the one hand, makes
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.82,0:34:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,your application a little bit
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.66,0:34:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,larger, because the vector data
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.27,0:34:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,takes up some space.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.85,0:34:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But on the other hand, will give
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.28,0:34:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you the opportunity to scale
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.96,0:34:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,these images, which might be
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.96,0:34:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,useful in a number of different
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.32,0:34:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,situations.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.87,0:34:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So, one is, if you know that
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.38,0:34:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,this particular image is going
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.62,0:34:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to be used at multiple sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.15,0:34:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But that might be less obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.64,0:34:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So, one case is a symbolic glyph
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.93,0:34:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that should resize with dynamic
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.48,0:34:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,type.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.95,0:34:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Since we're thinking about
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.83,0:34:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,dynamic type, you should also be
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.30,0:34:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking about having glyphs
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.71,0:34:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that are appearing next to type
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.22,0:34:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,resize appropriately.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.24,0:34:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Another case that's really not
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.00,0:34:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,obvious, is tab bar images.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.79,0:34:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you're probably used to your
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.39,0:34:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,tab bar images appearing at just
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.48,0:34:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,a single size.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.75,0:35:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's a really great
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.48,0:35:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibility feature that we
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.99,0:35:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,strongly recommend supporting,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.45,0:35:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that allows for user that have
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.72,0:35:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,turned their dynamic type size
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.45,0:35:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,up.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.79,0:35:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,When they tap and hold on a tab
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.71,0:35:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,bar image, a larger version
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.01,0:35:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,appears in the center of the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.22,0:35:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,screen in a Hud.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.81,0:35:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you swipe your finger you
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.24,0:35:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,can see different ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.01,0:35:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can support this in your
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.04,0:35:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,apps by returning a different
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.92,0:35:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,image to use for this purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.61,0:35:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you use PDF-backed images
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.23,0:35:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and preserve the vector data for
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.24,0:35:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,your tab bar images, it will
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.38,0:35:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,just happen by default.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.86,0:35:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we really recommend doing
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.35,0:35:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that to increase the usability
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.94,0:35:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of your app across all users.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.40,0:35:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.00,0:35:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And the final topic that I want
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.08,0:35:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to discuss, is ProMotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.00,0:35:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, as you heard, on certain new
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.69,0:35:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,iPads we're increasing the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.31,0:35:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,refresh rate of the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.87,0:35:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can find out what the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.36,0:35:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,screen's refresh rate is on a
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.59,0:35:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,particular device, by querying
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.38,0:35:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,this property on UIScreen.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.46,0:36:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So, once you've queried it, what
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.81,0:36:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,should you do with that
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.50,0:36:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,information?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.11,0:36:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it depends on what kind of
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.74,0:36:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,app you're building.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.68,0:36:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you have a UIKit
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.85,0:36:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,application, the answer is
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.25,0:36:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,actually you really shouldn't do
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.53,0:36:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,much with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.80,0:36:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The crucial thing for a UIKit
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.15,0:36:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,application, is you just want to
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.72,0:36:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,optimize your drawing code.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.53,0:36:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You just want to make sure that
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.76,0:36:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,you're getting your frame rate
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.25,0:36:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,as high as you can on all
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.71,0:36:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.18,0:36:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And to do that, we strongly
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.52,0:36:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,recommend using Instruments.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.02,0:36:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You can check out the frame rate
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.23,0:36:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're achieving during
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.44,0:36:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,scrolling and animations.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.65,0:36:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And find out what might be
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.77,0:36:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,bogging you down.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.79,0:36:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you do that, then it will
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.01,0:36:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,really improve the user
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.49,0:36:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,experience on your app across
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.78,0:36:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,all devices, including ones with
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.81,0:36:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,a higher screen refresh rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.52,0:36:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The situation is more
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.14,0:36:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,complicated for Metal apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.00,0:36:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for apps that are using
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.32,0:36:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Metal, you're going to want to
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.09,0:36:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,think more about what refresh
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.12,0:36:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,rates to try to hit in different
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.51,0:36:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,situations.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.65,0:36:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So, your goal here, is to ensure
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.60,0:37:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,smooth playback.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.67,0:37:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the past, you might have
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.31,0:37:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,been actually pessimistically
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.71,0:37:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,clamping your refresh rate to 30
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.49,0:37:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,frames per second to make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.98,0:37:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that the frame rate is smooth.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.39,0:37:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, on devices that support
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.93,0:37:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,higher screen refresh rates, you
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.30,0:37:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,could, for example, clamp to 40
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.89,0:37:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,frames per second to get a
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.85,0:37:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,better smooth playback
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.15,0:37:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,experience, since 40 divides
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.79,0:37:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,evenly into 120 frames per
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.14,0:37:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,second.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.42,0:37:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're showing cinematic
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.63,0:37:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,content, you might want to
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.69,0:37:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,choose a refresh rate of 24
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.21,0:37:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,frames per second, which now
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.35,0:37:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,also, will look really smooth on
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.85,0:37:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,these devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.81,0:37:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So, a lot of options, here.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.41,0:37:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You probably want to think about
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.64,0:37:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the content that you're
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.52,0:37:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,displaying to conserve power.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.15,0:37:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't want to be hitting 120
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.53,0:37:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,fps all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.57,0:37:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, you can use XCode's
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.37,0:37:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,GPU Report feature to look at
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.78,0:37:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the performance characteristics
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.06,0:37:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,of your Metal applications.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.14,0:37:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a session on
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.50,0:37:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Introducing Metal 2, that we
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.56,0:37:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,strongly recommend going to.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.14,0:37:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what's new.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.78,0:37:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'm going to hand it back
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.38,0:37:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,over to Josh.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.09,0:38:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.52,0:38:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.89,0:38:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thanks, Eliza.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.22,0:38:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We got a late start, this
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.23,0:38:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.58,0:38:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we're going to have a really
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.40,0:38:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,quick end, right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.74,0:38:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I have one last topic I wanted
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.45,0:38:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to talk about, really quickly,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.73,0:38:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and I promise this is really
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.79,0:38:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.17,0:38:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Localization is a really key
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.55,0:38:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,way to broaden the reach of your
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.13,0:38:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.20,0:38:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And for many people,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.91,0:38:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Localization can seem synonymous
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.98,0:38:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,with translation.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.17,0:38:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's actually more than
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.15,0:38:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.74,0:38:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And one quick thing I just want
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.50,0:38:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to mention is considering
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.19,0:38:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,layouts that are important for
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.40,0:38:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,localized applications.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.37,0:38:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So, take a look at this, really
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.34,0:38:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.76,0:38:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,For many of you, this probably
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.90,0:38:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,feels really comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.52,0:38:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you now, keep watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.82,0:38:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to change it, and
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.98,0:38:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,hopefully, make you feel kind of
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.12,0:38:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.37,0:38:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this probably seems really
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.72,0:38:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,backwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.84,0:38:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Labels are aligned weird, arrows
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.51,0:38:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,are in the wrong direction,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.72,0:38:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,animations happen the wrong way.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.98,0:38:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But believe it or not, this is
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.44,0:38:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,actually a real layout.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.98,0:38:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You just don't usually see it
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.91,0:38:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,with English.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.89,0:39:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You usually see it with a
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.11,0:39:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,language that reads right to
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.02,0:39:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,left, like Arabic or Hebrew.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.22,0:39:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, for a user that expects to
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.53,0:39:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,see this, this feels really
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.27,0:39:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,natural.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.27,0:39:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you felt comfortable with
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.40,0:39:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,this and uncomfortable with
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.29,0:39:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,this.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.10,0:39:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, now you know what someone
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.27,0:39:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,whose native language reads
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.68,0:39:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,right to left feels like if
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.43,0:39:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,they're not presented with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.27,0:39:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you want to make sure if
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.21,0:39:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you're localizing, that you also
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.16,0:39:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,support RTL in your layouts, if
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.58,0:39:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to support RTL
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.41,0:39:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.19,0:39:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the system is doing this
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.47,0:39:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.41,0:39:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Many teams have been spending a
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.75,0:39:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,lot of time to make sure that
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.14,0:39:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,this is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.65,0:39:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And in fact, UIKit does a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.42,0:39:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,it for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.24,0:39:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, navigation controllers and
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.53,0:39:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,switches will switch
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.57,0:39:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.62,0:39:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you're building your own
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.65,0:39:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,custom views, you definitely
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.68,0:39:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,want to take a look at your
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.61,0:39:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,layouts in RTL languages, as
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.17,0:39:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,well, if you localize in those
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.52,0:39:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.00,0:39:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that was my really quick
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.49,0:39:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,wrap-up on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.42,0:39:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Lots more information about
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.36,0:39:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,localization in the Localization
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.92,0:39:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Guide on developer.apple.com.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.10,0:39:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, there's plenty
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.50,0:39:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,more info available from this
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.31,0:39:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,session, and a ton of related
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.29,0:39:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,sessions, all week.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.33,0:40:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The four Drag and Drop sessions
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.50,0:40:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,are going to be great.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.18,0:40:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You definitely should check them
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.78,0:40:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,out.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.13,0:40:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Updating Your App for iOS 11 is
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.78,0:40:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,really going to be a great
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.74,0:40:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,session, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.84,0:40:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And make Eliza happy and go
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.23,0:40:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,check out the Introducing
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.36,0:40:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Password Autofill for Your Apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.03,0:40:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And implement that.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.16,0:40:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.88,0:40:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And enjoy the week.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.52,0:40:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
